66tesco-crop.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&strip=all\" data-orig-size=\"1200,1304\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{\"aperture\":\"0\",\"credit\":\"facebook\",\"camera\":\"\",\"caption\":\"tesco salford facebook post\",\"created_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"tesco salford\",\"orientation\":\"1\"}\" data-image-title=\"Women in pyjamas\" data-image-description=\"<p>tesco salford facebook post</p> \" data-medium-file=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/01/ad230608366tesco-crop.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&w=276&strip=all\" data-large-file=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/01/ad230608366tesco-crop.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&w=942&strip=all\" class=\"img-align-center size-full wp-image-6361946\" src=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/01/ad230608366tesco-crop.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&strip=all\" alt=\"Who doesn't want to be comfortable while doing the big shop (Picture: Facebook)\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1113\" /></a></div><figcaption>Who doesn’t want to be comfortable while doing the big shop (Picture: Facebook)</figcaption></figure> <strong>A man who complained about shoppers wearing pyjamas while in Tesco has been ribbed senseless online.</strong>\nChris Cooke left a strongly-worded comment on Tesco’s Facebook page, calling two women he’d spotted in the Salford store ‘bloody disgusting’ for browsing the aisles in their PJs.\n<a href=\"http://metro.co.uk/2017/01/04/newborn-baby-dumped-in-a-bin-with-tissues-stuffed-in-his-mouth-6360600/\" data-track=\"thumbnail-link\" data-track-destination=\"6360600\" class=\"thumbnail-link\"><img src=\"http://i0.wp.com/metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/01/ad_230563338.jpg?crop=137px%2C0px%2C2226px%2C1670px&resize=150%2C113&quality=80&strip=all&ssl=1&w=100&h=75\" data-aspect=\"1.3274336283186\" alt=\"Mother admits dumping baby in a bin (Getty) An ambulance is parked outside the Accident and Emergency department of the Accident and Emergency department of the 'Royal Albert Edward Infirmary' in Wigan, north west England on April 2, 2015. AFP PHOTO / OLI SCARFF (Photo credit should read OLI SCARFF/AFP/Getty Images)\" class=\"thumbnail-link-image\" data-rewritten=\"false\" /><span class=\"mor-title\">Newborn baby dumped in a bin with tissues stuffed in his mouth</span></a> He ranted: ‘Dear Tesco, please a rule in place that people like this will not be served in your stores. It’s bloody disgusting.’\nCooke said that he’d spotted the women at around 7pm, but they were by no means the only offenders. He’s seen others committing the same heinous crime.\n<figure class=\"aligncenter img-container shareable-item\" style=\"max-width:620px\"><div class=\"img-wrap\"><a id=\"item-attachment_6361945\" class=\"anchor\"></a><div class=\"item-share-buttons item-share\"><a class=\"share-item share-item-facebook btn\" title=\"Share this on Facebook\" data-track=\"share-item-facebook\"><span class=\"icon icon-facebook\"></span></a><a class=\"share-item share-item-twitter btn\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Share this on Twitter\" data-track=\"share-item-twitter\"><span class=\"icon icon-twitter\"></span></a><a class=\"share-item share-item-pinterest btn\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Share this on Pinterest\" data-track=\"share-item-pinterest\"><span class=\"icon icon-pinterest\"></span></a></div><a href=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/01/ad230608366tesco-salford-fa.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&strip=all\"><img data-attachment-id=\"6361945\" data-permalink=\"http://metro.co.uk/?attachment_id=6361945\" data-orig-file=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/01/ad230608366tesco-salford-fa.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&strip=all\" data-orig-size=\"810,539\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{\"aperture\":\"0\",\"credit\":\"facebook\",\"camera\":\"\",\"caption\":\"tesco salford facebook post\",\"created_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"tesco salford\",\"orientation\":\"1\"}\" data-image-title=\"Women in pyjamas\" data-image-description=\"<p>tesco salford facebook post</p> \" data-medium-file=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/01/ad230608366tesco-salford-fa.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&w=300&strip=all\" data-large-file=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/01/ad230608366tesco-salford-fa.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&w=810&strip=all\" class=\"img-align-center size-full wp-image-6361945\" src=\"https://metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/01/ad230608366tesco-salford-fa.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&strip=all\" alt=\"(Picture: Facebook)\" width=\"810\" height=\"539\" /></a></div><figcaption>(Picture: Facebook)</figcaption></figure> He added: ‘Who doesn’t have the time to get changed into clothes to go shopping?’\nUnsurprisingly, many jumped on the judgemental post and poor Cooke was ridiculed.\n<fb:post href=\"https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=10157934693190109&set=o.112463368812803&type=3&theater\"></fb:post>\nJoel Brackenbury mocked his post by appealing to the supermarket giant to make a rule that people like Mr Cooke would not be served in stores. ‘I for one find it uncomfortable to have to shop alongside people who spend their time taking photographs of strangers minding their own business rather than just ignoring things that do not affect them in any way, and have seen other people before making complaints on a similar basis.\n<a href=\"http://metro.co.uk/2017/01/04/stag-in-court-after-having-tantrum-when-cabin-crew-refused-to-serve-him-alcohol-6360915/\" data-track=\"thumbnail-link\" data-track-destination=\"6360915\" class=\"thumbnail-link\"><img src=\"http://i0.wp.com/metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/01/syag-splt.jpg?crop=180px%2C0px%2C842px%2C630px&resize=150%2C113&quality=80&strip=all&ssl=1&w=100&h=75\" data-aspect=\"1.3274336283186\" class=\"thumbnail-link-image\" data-rewritten=\"false\" /><span class=\"mor-title\">Stag in court after having tantrum when cabin crew refused to serve him alcohol</span></a> ‘I mean who doesn’t have the time to just ignore these women and carry on shopping?’\nMeanwhile a Tesco spokeswoman replied: ‘Many of our customers have told us that they feel uncomfortable when they see other shoppers wearing unsuitable clothing in our stores and we do try to find a balance that everyone is happy with.\n‘Although we don’t have a formal dress code in our stores, we rely on our management team to use their discretion and common sense.’\nThe Tesco customer care representative also pledged to log Cooke’s complaint in the firm’s systems for review.\n<aside class=\"zone-post-strip\"><h3>More: <a href=\"https://metrouk2.wordpress.com/news/uk/\" data-track=\"zone-post-strip-more\">UK</a></h3><div class=\"zopo-item\"><a href=\"http://metro.co.uk/2017/01/05/vigil-for-stud-badboy-shot-by-police-as-friends-and-family-seek-justice-for-yassar-6361912\" class=\"zopo-link\" data-track=\"zone-post-strip-item\" data-track-destination=\"6361912\"><img src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhEAAJAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAE L QAAkAAAIKhI+py+0Po5yUFQA7\" data-src=\"http://i1.wp.com/metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/01/yassasr.jpg?crop=410px%2C38px%2C790px%2C592px&resize=480%2C360&quality=80&strip=all&ssl=1&w=170&h=128\" data-aspect=\"1. \" data-rewritten=\"false\" width=\"170\" height=\"128\" /><span>Vigil for 'Stud Badboy' shot by police as friends and family seek 'justice for Yassar'</span>\n</a></div><div class=\"zopo-item\"><a href=\"http://metro.co.uk/2017/01/04/shoppers-stunned-by-toy-hamsters-sex-noises-6361849\" class=\"zopo-link\" data-track=\"zone-post-strip-item\" data-track-destination=\"6361849\"><img src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhEAAJAIAAAP///wAAACH5BAE L QAAkAAAIKhI+py+0Po5yUFQA7\" data-src=\"http://i0.wp.com/metrouk2.files.wordpress.com/2017/01/ac_debenhams_hamster_comp.jpg?crop=359px%2C0px%2C841px%2C630px&resize=480%2C360&quality=80&strip=all&ssl=1&w=170&h=128\" data-aspect=\"1. \" data-rewritten=\"false\" width=\"170\" height=